doc.after: Dartmouth is well known for its fierce school spirit and many traditions.[158] The college functions on a quarter system, and one weekend each term is set aside as a traditional celebratory event, known on campus as "big weekends"[159][160] or "party weekends".[161] In the fall term, Homecoming (officially called Dartmouth Night) is marked by a bonfire on the Green constructed by the freshman class.[162] Winter term is celebrated by Winter Carnival, a tradition started in 1911 by the Dartmouth Outing Club to promote winter sports.[163] In the spring, Green Key is a weekend mostly devoted to campus parties and celebration.[164]
